comment.author: 47524421@N08
comment._content:
Although the digits '1885' are visible on the tail, there is evidence that the front part of the serial number has been overpainted.  So this could be:

Consolidated B-24M-5-CO Liberator 44-41885, which went to the RAAF as A72-147, named THERESA ANNE, served with 25 Sqn as SJ-H sold June 1950.
